## Code Style (enforced on every test file)

- **No `//` or `///`.** All comments are block-style `/* */` or JSDoc `/** */`.
- **No em or en dashes.** U+2014 (EM DASH) and U+2013 (EN DASH) are banned.
  Use hyphen, colon, comma, parentheses, or rephrase.
- **File header** - open every test file with `@file` + `@description`:

  ```typescript
  /**
   * @file MyContract.test.ts
   * @description Hardhat tests for MyContract: [what it covers].
   */
  ```

- **Section dividers** are asterisk-bordered box comments, one line each:

  ```typescript
  /*************** Minting ***************/
  /*************** Transfer ***************/
  /*************** ACL Invariants ***************/
  ```

  At least 10 leading and 10 trailing `*`, Title Case label. Use one
  divider per `describe` group if the file has more than two.

- **Test helpers / exported fixtures** use JSDoc (NOT NatSpec - NatSpec is
  Solidity-only). Leading description text plus `@param`, `@returns`,
  `@throws`, `@example`, `@deprecated`, `@see`, `@remarks` (TSDoc). Never
  `@notice`, `@dev`, `@inheritdoc`, or `@custom:*` in test files.

  ```typescript
  /**
   * Encrypt a euint64 and mint it to `to` in one step.
   *
   * @param token The deployed ConfidentialERC20 instance.
   * @param to Recipient signer.
   * @param amount Cleartext amount, bigint.
   * @returns The decrypted on-chain balance after the mint.
   * @throws If the signer lacks minter permission.
   */
  async function mintAndRead(token, to, amount) { }
  ```

- **Inline comments** explain WHY, not WHAT: why this assertion enforces
  a specific FHE invariant, why this handle order matters, why this edge
  case would otherwise pass silently.

